<DocsLayout title="API Keys">
  <h1>API Keys</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-slate-400">Programmatic access for automation and integrations.</p>

  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p><strong>API keys</strong> provide programmatic access to Datanika's API. Use them to trigger runs, query status, or integrate with CI/CD pipelines and external tools.</p>

  <h3>Properties</h3>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>name</code></td><td>Descriptive name (e.g., "CI/CD pipeline key")</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>scopes</code></td><td>Permission scopes limiting what the key can access</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>expires_at</code></td><td>Optional expiration date</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>last_used_at</code></td><td>Timestamp of last usage (tracked automatically)</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>API keys are displayed <strong>only once</strong> at creation. Store them securely.</li>
    <li>Keys are hashed with bcrypt before storage — we cannot recover a lost key.</li>
    <li>Each key is tied to a specific user and organization.</li>
    <li>Set an expiration date for keys used in temporary workflows.</li>
    <li>Revoke keys instantly from the settings page.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How to create an API key</h2>
  <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-2">
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Settings</strong> in the sidebar</li>
    <li>Scroll to the <strong>API Keys</strong> section</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Create API Key</strong></li>
    <li>Enter a descriptive name (e.g., "CI/CD pipeline key")</li>
    <li>Select the permission <strong>scopes</strong> the key should have</li>
    <li>Optionally set an <strong>expiration date</strong></li>
    <li>Click <strong>Create</strong> — the key is displayed <strong>only once</strong>, so copy and store it securely</li>
  </ol>
  <p>To revoke a key, click <strong>Delete</strong> next to it in the API Keys table. Revocation is immediate.</p>

  <h2>Usage</h2>
  <p>Include the API key in the <code>Authorization</code> header:</p>
  <pre><code>curl -H "Authorization: Bearer dnk_your_api_key_here" \
     https://app.datanika.io/api/v1/runs</code></pre>

  <h3>Example</h3>
  <pre><code>API Key: "GitHub Actions deploy key"
Scopes: [runs.create, runs.read]
Expires: 2027-01-01
Created by: alice@acme.com</code></pre>
</DocsLayout>
